The paper discusses multi-modal analysis in multimedia, which involves processing and analyzing heterogeneous and multi-modal data from different modalities such as texts, images, videos, audios, etc. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including multimedia (cs.MM), computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM, followed by cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.CL.
